{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We look around the media, as we see on the news from Iraq,"},{"time":3000,"text":"Afghanistan, Sierra Leone,"},{"time":6000,"text":"and the conflict seems incomprehensible to us."},{"time":10000,"text":"And that's certainly how it seemed to me when I started this project."},{"time":14000,"text":"But as a physicist,"},{"time":16000,"text":"I thought, well if you give me some data,"},{"time":19000,"text":"I could maybe understand this. You know, give us a go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"So as a naive New Zealander"},{"time":23000,"text":"I thought, well I'll go to the Pentagon."},{"time":25000,"text":"Can you get me some information?"},{"time":27000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":30000,"text":"No. So I had to think a little harder."},{"time":34000,"text":"And I was watching the news one night in Oxford."},{"time":37000,"text":"And I looked down at the chattering heads on my channel of choice."},{"time":40000,"text":"And I saw that there was information there."},{"time":42000,"text":"There was data within the streams of news that we consume."},{"time":45000,"text":"All this noise around us actually has information."},{"time":49000,"text":"So what I started thinking was,"},{"time":51000,"text":"perhaps there is something like open source intelligence here."},{"time":54000,"text":"If we can get enough of these streams of information together,"},{"time":57000,"text":"we can perhaps start to understand the war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"So this is exactly what I did. We started bringing a team together,"},{"time":63000,"text":"an interdisciplinary team of scientists,"},{"time":65000,"text":"of economists, mathematicians."},{"time":68000,"text":"We brought these guys together and we started to try and solve this."},{"time":71000,"text":"We did it in three steps."},{"time":73000,"text":"The first step we did was to collect. We did 130 different sources of information --"},{"time":77000,"text":"from NGO reports to newspapers and cable news."},{"time":80000,"text":"We brought this raw data in and we filtered it."},{"time":83000,"text":"We extracted the key bits on information to build the database."},{"time":86000,"text":"That database contained"},{"time":88000,"text":"the timing of attacks,"},{"time":90000,"text":"the location, the size and the weapons used."},{"time":92000,"text":"It's all in the streams of information we consume daily,"},{"time":95000,"text":"we just have to know how to pull it out."},{"time":97000,"text":"And once we had this we could start doing some cool stuff."},{"time":99000,"text":"What if we were to look at the distribution of the sizes of attacks?"},{"time":102000,"text":"What would that tell us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"So we started doing this. And you can see here"},{"time":106000,"text":"on the horizontal axis"},{"time":108000,"text":"you've got the number of people killed in an attack"},{"time":110000,"text":"or the size of the attack."},{"time":112000,"text":"And on the vertical axis you've got the number of attacks."},{"time":115000,"text":"So we plot data for sample on this."},{"time":117000,"text":"You see some sort of random distribution --"},{"time":119000,"text":"perhaps 67 attacks, one person was killed,"},{"time":122000,"text":"or 47 attacks where seven people were killed."},{"time":125000,"text":"We did this exact same thing for Iraq."},{"time":127000,"text":"And we didn't know, for Iraq what we were going to find."},{"time":130000,"text":"It turns out what we found was pretty surprising."},{"time":134000,"text":"You take all of the conflict,"},{"time":136000,"text":"all of the chaos, all of the noise,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and out of that"},{"time":140000,"text":"comes this precise mathematical distribution"},{"time":142000,"text":"of the way attacks are ordered in this conflict."},{"time":145000,"text":"This blew our mind."},{"time":147000,"text":"Why should a conflict like Iraq have this"},{"time":151000,"text":"as its fundamental signature?"},{"time":153000,"text":"Why should there be order in war?"},{"time":155000,"text":"We didn't really understand that."},{"time":157000,"text":"We thought maybe there is something special about Iraq."},{"time":161000,"text":"So we looked at a few more conflicts."},{"time":163000,"text":"We looked at Colombia, we looked at Afghanistan,"},{"time":165000,"text":"and we looked at Senegal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"And the same pattern emerged in each conflict."},{"time":169000,"text":"This wasn't supposed to happen."},{"time":171000,"text":"These are different wars, with different religious factions,"},{"time":174000,"text":"different political factions, and different socioeconomic problems."},{"time":177000,"text":"And yet the fundamental patterns underlying them"},{"time":181000,"text":"are the same."},{"time":184000,"text":"So we went a little wider."},{"time":186000,"text":"We looked around the world at all the data we could get our hands on."},{"time":189000,"text":"From Peru to Indonesia,"},{"time":192000,"text":"we studied this same pattern again."},{"time":194000,"text":"And we found that not only"},{"time":197000,"text":"were the distributions these straight lines,"},{"time":199000,"text":"but the slope of these lines, they clustered around"},{"time":201000,"text":"this value of alpha equals 2.5."},{"time":204000,"text":"And we could generate an equation"},{"time":206000,"text":"that could predict the likelihood of an attack."},{"time":209000,"text":"What we're saying here"},{"time":211000,"text":"is the probability of an attack killing X number of people"},{"time":215000,"text":"in a country like Iraq"},{"time":217000,"text":"is equal to a constant, times the size of that attack,"},{"time":220000,"text":"raised to the power of negative alpha."},{"time":223000,"text":"And negative alpha is the slope of that line I showed you before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"So what?"},{"time":231000,"text":"This is data, statistics. What does it tell us about these conflicts?"},{"time":234000,"text":"That was a challenge we had to face as physicists."},{"time":237000,"text":"How do we explain this?"},{"time":240000,"text":"And what we really found was that alpha,"},{"time":242000,"text":"if we think about it, is the organizational"},{"time":244000,"text":"structure of the insurgency."},{"time":247000,"text":"Alpha is the distribution of the sizes of attacks,"},{"time":250000,"text":"which is really the distribution"},{"time":252000,"text":"of the group strength carrying out the attacks."},{"time":254000,"text":"So we look at a process of group dynamics:"},{"time":256000,"text":"coalescence and fragmentation,"},{"time":259000,"text":"groups coming together, groups breaking apart."},{"time":261000,"text":"And we start running the numbers on this. Can we simulate it?"},{"time":264000,"text":"Can we create the kind of patterns that we're seeing"},{"time":267000,"text":"in places like Iraq?"},{"time":270000,"text":"Turns out we kind of do a reasonable job."},{"time":272000,"text":"We can run these simulations."},{"time":274000,"text":"We can recreate this using a process of group dynamics"},{"time":277000,"text":"to explain the patterns that we see"},{"time":279000,"text":"all around the conflicts around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"So what's going on?"},{"time":286000,"text":"Why should these different -- seemingly different conflicts"},{"time":289000,"text":"have the same patterns?"},{"time":291000,"text":"Now what I believe is going on is that"},{"time":294000,"text":"the insurgent forces, they evolve over time. They adapt."},{"time":298000,"text":"And it turns out there is only one solution"},{"time":300000,"text":"to fight a much stronger enemy."},{"time":302000,"text":"And if you don't find that solution as an insurgent force,"},{"time":305000,"text":"you don't exist."},{"time":307000,"text":"So every insurgent force that is ongoing,"},{"time":309000,"text":"every conflict that is ongoing,"},{"time":311000,"text":"it's going to look something like this."},{"time":313000,"text":"And that is what we think is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"Taking it forward, how do we change it?"},{"time":318000,"text":"How do we end a war like Iraq?"},{"time":320000,"text":"What does it look like?"},{"time":322000,"text":"Alpha is the structure. It's got a stable state at 2.5."},{"time":325000,"text":"This is what wars look like when they continue."},{"time":329000,"text":"We've got to change that."},{"time":331000,"text":"We can push it up:"},{"time":333000,"text":"the forces become more fragmented;"},{"time":335000,"text":"there is more of them, but they are weaker."},{"time":339000,"text":"Or we push it down:"},{"time":341000,"text":"they're more robust; there is less groups;"},{"time":343000,"text":"but perhaps you can sit and talk to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"So this graph here, I'm going to show you now."},{"time":349000,"text":"No one has seen this before. This is literally"},{"time":352000,"text":"stuff that we've come through last week."},{"time":354000,"text":"And we see the evolution of Alpha through time."},{"time":358000,"text":"We see it start. And we see it grow up to the stable state"},{"time":361000,"text":"the wars around the world look like."},{"time":363000,"text":"And it stays there through the invasion of Fallujah"},{"time":366000,"text":"until the Samarra bombings in the"},{"time":368000,"text":"Iraqi elections of '06."},{"time":371000,"text":"And the system gets perturbed. It moves upwards"},{"time":373000,"text":"to a fragmented state."},{"time":375000,"text":"This is when the surge happens."},{"time":377000,"text":"And depending on who you ask,"},{"time":379000,"text":"the surge was supposed to push it up even further."},{"time":382000,"text":"The opposite happened."},{"time":384000,"text":"The groups became stronger."},{"time":386000,"text":"They became more robust."},{"time":388000,"text":"And so I'm thinking, right, great, it's going to keep going down."},{"time":391000,"text":"We can talk to them. We can get a solution. The opposite happened."},{"time":394000,"text":"It's moved up again. The groups are more fragmented."},{"time":397000,"text":"And this tells me one of two things."},{"time":399000,"text":"Either we're back where we started"},{"time":402000,"text":"and the surge has had no effect;"},{"time":404000,"text":"or finally the groups have been fragmented to the extent"},{"time":408000,"text":"that we can start to think about maybe moving out."},{"time":412000,"text":"I don't know what the answer is to that."},{"time":414000,"text":"But I know that we should be looking at the structure of the insurgency"},{"time":417000,"text":"to answer that question."},{"time":419000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":421000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}